# Vulnerability allowlist for `make sbom-scan`. trivy auto-loads this file
# from the working directory.
#
# Each entry MUST carry a comment explaining:
#   * which SBOM(s) it applies to
#   * why it can't be fixed by bumping (i.e. upstream-blocked vs. accepted risk)
#   * a re-evaluation trigger (a release to watch for, a date to revisit)
#
# Entries here are the only way to silence a Critical CVE that the gate is
# blocking. Review periodically; remove anything that has been upstream-fixed.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# CVE-2025-68121 — crypto/tls cert-validation flaw in Go stdlib 1.22.5/1.23.6/
# 1.24.1; fixed in Go 1.24.13 / 1.25.7. Surfaces in:
#   * sbom-k8s-registry.k8s.io_kubectl_*.json — the kubectl binary is built
#     with Go 1.23.6 by the upstream Kubernetes release pipeline. Even
#     registry.k8s.io/kubectl:v1.34.0 still ships with this Go build.
#   * sbom-terraform.json — multiple TF providers (linode, hashicorp/*)
#     compiled with Go 1.22.5 / 1.24.1. Already on latest-available provider
#     versions in `.terraform.lock.hcl`.
# Re-evaluate when K8s ships a v1.32.x patch built with Go 1.24.13+, and when
# linode/linode + hashicorp/* providers cut releases on patched Go.
CVE-2025-68121

# CVE-2026-33186 — grpc-go denial of service (large header). Fixed in 1.79.3.
# Surfaces in sbom-terraform.json only:
#   * provider builds with google.golang.org/grpc v1.63.2 and v1.72.1 baked in.
# Already on latest-available provider versions. Re-evaluate when the
# upstream provider releases ship grpc-go >= 1.79.3.
CVE-2026-33186

# CVE-2026-31789 — openssl libcrypto3/libssl3 cert-validation flaw, fixed in
# 3.3.7-r0 / 3.0.19-1~deb12u2 depending on base. We track this only for the
# `maniator/gh:v2.92.0` alpine base — the openssl install is used by the gh
# CLI's outbound TLS to api.github.com; a malicious-
# server-induced cert flaw is not relevant in that direction. Other images
# that previously carried this CVE (alpine/curl, curlimages/curl, openbao,
# kubectl swap, promtail) have all been bumped to fixed bases.
# Re-evaluate when maniator/gh refreshes its base image past openssl 3.3.7.
CVE-2026-31789
